.TH "ipv6_dev_find" 9 "ipv6_dev_find" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipv6_dev_find \- find the first device with a given source address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct net_device *" ipv6_dev_find
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const struct in6_addr *addr "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
the net namespace
.IP "addr" 12
the source address
.IP "dev" 12
used to find the L3 domain of interest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The caller should be protected by RCU, or RTNL.
